					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-555395#post-1562751</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-555395/into-that-good-night#post-1562751</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 12 Sep 2012 07:02:53 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>eric_h</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>474585</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It wasn't an intentional metaphor. I wish I were that clever&#8230;</p> <p>I actually wrote 506 based on a dream I had. In the dream, the zucchini wasn't quite the same as in 506; it was less virulent in that it would only grow in soil (and other media in which plants can normally grow). It was edible and had solved the world hunger problem, but in a bizarre and annoying way. It did grow almost instantly, and it was everywhere, so it was essentially free food for anyone who wanted it. But because it grew so quickly and invasively, it had become incredibly expensive and labor-intensive to grow anything else. People tried to make interesting things out of it like zucchini flour, but it didn't work very well in the sense that everyone hated the stuff. &quot;Go eat zucchini!&quot; was a common curse you would hear&#8230;</p> <p>This is probably more interesting than the way I actually wrote it up, but I couldn't figure out how to describe &quot;zucchini world&quot; in the context of an SCP. It was easier to explain as a containment-worthy object by making it completely useless (and dangerous).</p> <p>You may have guessed that I have really strange dreams. Unfortunately, I don't usually remember them, or I would have no shortage of SCP ideas.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-555395#post-1562712</guid>
